=center|5\n|align=center|81\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2012}}\n|[[Donny Montell]]\n|English\n|\"[[Love Is Blind (Donny Montell song)|Love Is Blind]]\"\n|align=center|14\n|align=center|70\n|bgcolor=\"#CC9966\" align=center|3\n|bgcolor=\"#CC9966\" align=center|104\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2013}}\n|[[Andrius Pojavis]]\n|English\n|\"[[Something (Andrius Pojavis song)|Something]]\"\n|align=center|22\n|align=center|17\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|53\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2014}}\n|[[Vilija Mata\u010di\u016bnait\u0117|Vilija]]\n|English\n|\"[[Attention (Vilija Mata\u010di\u016bnait\u0117 song)|Attention]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|11\n|align=center|36\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2015}}\n|[[Monika Linkyt\u0117]] & [[Vaidas Baumila]]\n|English\n|\"[[This Time (Monika Linkyt\u0117 & Vaidas Baumila song)|This Time]]\"\n|align=center|18\n|align=center|30\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|67\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2016}}\n|[[Donny Montell]]\n|English\n|\"[[I've Been Waiting for This Night]]\"\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|200\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|222\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2017}}\n|[[Fusedmarc]]\n|English\n|\"[[Rain of Revolution]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|17\n|align=center|42\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2018}}\n|[[Ieva Zasimauskait\u0117]]\n|English{{efn|Contains two lines in Lithuanian.}}\n|\"[[When We're Old (Ieva Zasimauskait\u0117 song)|When We're Old]]\"\n|align=center|12\n|align=center|181\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|119\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2019}}\n|[[Jurijus Veklenko|Jurij Veklenko]]\n|English\n|\"[[Run with the Lions]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|11\n|align=center|93\n|-bgcolor=\"#87A96B\"\n|{{N/A|{{Escyr|2020}}}}{{Efn|2020 contest was cancelled due to 2019-20 pandemic of Coronavirus.}}\n|[[The Roop]]\n|English\n|\"[[On Fire (The Roop song)|On Fire]]\"\n|colspan=\"4\" {{N/A|Cancelled}}\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n===Barbara Dex Award===\n{{further|Barbara Dex Award}}\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!Year\n!Performer\n!Host city\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2014}}\n|[[Vilija Mata\u010di\u016bnait\u0117]]\n|{{flagicon|Denmark}} [[Copenhagen]]\n|{{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wiwibloggs.com/2015/07/09/poll-worst-dressed-barbara-dex-award-winner/|title=Poll: Who was the worst dressed Barbara Dex Award winner?|publisher=[[Wiwibloggs]]|date=9 July 2015|accessdate=8 December 2019|first=William Lee|last=Adams}}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n==Related involvement==\n===Commentators and spokespersons===\n{{more citations needed section|date=December 2019}}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Commentator\n!Spokesperson\n!class=\"unsortable\"|{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1994}}\n|[[Darius U\u017ekuraitis]] ||Gitana Lapinskait\u0117 ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1995}}-{{Escyr|1998}}\n|{{n/a|No broadcast}} ||{{n/a|Did not participate}} ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1999}}\n|rowspan=\"18\"|Darius U\u017ekuraitis ||[[Andrius Tapinas]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2000}}\n|{{n/a|Did not participate}} ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2001}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Loreta Tarozait\u0117]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2002}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2003}}\n|{{n/a|Did not participate}} ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2004}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Rolandas Vilkon\u010dius]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2005}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2006}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Lavija \u0160urnait\u0117]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2007}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2008}}\n|Rolandas Vilkon\u010dius ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2009}}\n|[[Ignas Krupavi\u010dius]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2010}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Giedrius Masalskis]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2011}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2012}}\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Ignas Krupavi\u010dius ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2013}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2014}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2015}}\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Ugn\u0117 Galadauskait\u0117]] ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2016}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2017}}\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Darius U\u017ekuraitis and [[Ger\u016bta Grini\u016bt\u0117]]|| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Egl\u0117 Daug\u0117lait\u0117]] ||{{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lrt.lt/projektai/eurovizija/naujienos/31/171667/d_uzkuraitis_eurovizija_siemet_komentuos_ne_vienas#skip|title=D. U\u017ekuraitis \u201eEurovizij\u0105\u201c \u0161iemet komentuos ne vienas - LRT|website=Lietuvos Radijas ir Televizija|date=5 May 2017|accessdate=3 May 2018|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170805181800/http://www.lrt.lt/projektai/eurovizija/naujienos/31/171667/d_uzkuraitis_eurovizija_siemet_komentuos_ne_vienas#skip|archivedate=5 August 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lrt.lt/naujienos/eurovizija/31/171602/eurovizinius_lietuvos_balus_siemet_skelbs_e_daugelaite|title=Eurovizinius Lietuvos balus \u0161iemet skelbs E. Daug\u0117lait\u0117||date=2 May 2017|website=lrt.lt|accessdate=2 May 2017}}</ref>}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2018}}\n|\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2019}}\n|Giedrius Masalskis ||\n|}\n\n===Conductors===\n* Tomas Leiburas ({{Escyr|1994}})<ref>{{cite web|url=http://andtheconductoris.eu/|title=And the conductor is...|website=andtheconductoris.eu|accessdate=19 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Photogallery==\n<gallery class=\"center\">\nFile:Linas and Simona - Lithuania 2004.jpg|[[Linas and Simona]] in Istanbul ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2004|2004]])\nFile:4fun Eurovision 2007.jpg|[[4Fun]] in Helsinki ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2007|2007]])\nFile:ImageESC 2008 - Lithuania - Jeronimas Milius, 2nd semifinal.jpg|[[Jeronimas Milius]] in Belgrade ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2008|2008]])\nFile:Esc son.jpg|[[Sasha Son]] in Moscow ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2009|2009]])\nFile:Inculto band.jpg|[[Inculto|InCulto]] in Oslo ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2010|2010]])\nFile:ESC2013 - Lithuania 02.jpg|[[Andrius Pojavis]] in Malm\u00f6 ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2013|2013]])\nFile:ESC2014 - Lithuania 01.jpg|[[Vilija Mata\u010di\u016bnait\u0117|Vilija]] in Copenhagen ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2014|2014]])\nFile:20150516 ESC 2015 Monika Linkyt\u0117 & Vaidas Baumila 7568.jpg|[[Monika Linkyt\u0117]] & [[Vaidas Baumila]] in Vienna ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2015|2015]])\nFile:ESC2016 - Lithuania 07.jpg|[[Donny Montell]] in Stockholm ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2016|2016]])\nFile:Eurovision Song Contest 2017, Semi Final 2 Rehearsals. Photo 264.jpg|[[Fusedmarc]] in Kyiv ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2017|2017]])\nfile:Ieva Zasimauskait\u0117 (Lithuania 2018).jpg|[[Ieva Zasimauskait\u0117]] in Lisbon ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2018|2018]])\nfile:ESC2019-Lithuania.jpg|[[Jurijus Veklenko|Jurij Veklenko]] in Tel Aviv ([[Eurovision Song Contest 2019|2019]])\n</gallery>\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.eurovisioncovers.co.uk/xtlit.htm Points to and from Lithuania] ''eurovisioncovers.co.uk''\n\n{{Lithuania in Eurovision}}\n{{Eurovision Song Contest}}\n\n[[Category:Countries in the Eurovision Song Contest]]\n[[Category:Lithuania in the Eurovision Song Contest]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song contest country\n| Name = Lithuania\n| Member station = [[Lithuanian National Radio and Television]] (LRT)\n| National selection event = \n{{Collapsible list\n | title = '''Internal selection'''\n | 1994\n}}\n{{Collapsible list\n | title = '''National final'''\n | 1999\n | 2001\u20132002\n | 2004\u20132008\n | '''Lietuvos Dain\u0173 Daina'''\n | 2009\n | '''Eurovizija'''\n | 2010\u20132012\n | '''\"Eurovizijos\" dain\u0173 konkurso nacionalin\u0117 atranka'''\n | 2013\u20132019\n | '''Pabandom i\u0161 naujo!'''\n | 2021\n}}\n| ESC apps = 20 (13 finals)\n| ESC first = {{Escyr|1994}}\n| ESC last = \n| ESC best = 6th: {{Escyr|2006}}\n| ESC worst = Last {{small|SF}}: {{Escyr|2005}}\n| Nul points = {{Escyr|1994}}\n| Website = \n| EBU page = https://eurovision.tv/country/lithuania\n| Current = 2019\n}}\n\n'''Lithuania''' has participated in the '''Eurovision Song Contest''' (known in Lithuania as ''Eurovizijos dain\u0173 konkursas'') 20 times since its debut in [[Eurovision Song Contest 1994|1994]], where  [[Ovidijus Vy\u0161niauskas]] finished last, receiving [[Voting_at_the_Eurovision_Song_Contest#Scoring_no_points|\"nul points\"]]. Lithuania  withdrew from the contest, not returning until [[Eurovision Song Contest 1999|1999]]. [[LT United]]'s sixth place in {{escyr|2006}} with the song \"[[We Are the Winners]]\" is Lithuania's best result in the contest. The country reached the top ten for a second time in {{escyr|2016}}, when [[Donny Montell]] finished ninth with \"[[I've Been Waiting for This Night]]\".\n\n==History==\n===2000s===\nHaving been relegated from the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2000|2000 contest]] the country returned in 2001 with [[Skamp]] and \"[[You Got Style]]\", the first Lithuanian song to include [[English language|English]]. They received 35 points, placing 13th. However the following year, [[Aivaras]] could only manage to come second last with 12 points.\n\nSince the semi-finals were introduced Lithuania again came last with Laura and the Lovers and \"[[Little by Little (Laura & The Lovers song)|Little by Little]]\". The following year the Lithuanian broadcaster [[Lithuanian National Radio and Television|Lietuvos Nacionalinis Radijas ir Televizija]] (LRT) sent [[LT United]] to the 2006 contest with the [[football chant]]-like song \"[[We Are the Winners]]\". They took Lithuania to the final for the first time since 2002, coming sixth in the final with 162 points, Lithuania's best placing as of 2019.\n\nThe following year Lithuania automatically qualified for the final, however [[4Fun]] could not replicate LT United's success, coming 21st with only 28 points, 12 of which came from [[Ireland in the Eurovision Song Contest|Ireland]]. In 2008 [[Jeronimas Milius]] failed to reach the final, coming 16th of 19 competing nations in the second semi-final.\n\nLithuania threatened to boycott the 2009 contest \"if Russia continues to showcase power and ignores international law\". The statement was made in reaction to the Russia's actions in the [[2008 South Ossetia war]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.esckaz.com/2008/ |title=Lithuanian Broadcaster Head supports his Estonian colleague in Eurovision boycott |publisher=ESCKaz |date=2008-08-22 |accessdate=2008-08-22 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314020049/http://esckaz.com/2008/ |archivedate=2012-03-14 }}</ref> Culture Minister Jonas Jucas stated that it was too early to discuss the boycott since \"spontaneous decisions might aggravate the efforts of diplomats\" and thus make the situation worse. At the [[Eurovision Song Contest 2009]], Lithuania qualified from the semi finals and at the end of the voting in the final had received 23 points, placing them 23rd.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.baltic-course.com/eng/baltics_cis/?doc=4406|title=Culture minister of Lithuania: too early to speak about boycott of Eurovision|last=Vaida|first=Petras|date=2008-08-25|publisher=The Baltic Course|accessdate=2008-08-25|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090522023432/http://www.baltic-course.com/eng/baltics_cis/?doc=4406|archivedate=2009-05-22}}</ref>\n\n===2010s===\nLRT announced in December 2009 that, due to a lack of necessary funds, Lithuania would formally withdraw from the 2010 Contest. However, in the event that the necessary funds of 300,000 [[Lithuanian litas|litas]] ([[Euro|\u20ac]]90,000) would be found the broadcaster announced that they would attempt to continue the country's participation.<ref name=\"Lithuania\">{{cite web|url=http://www.esctoday.com/news/read/14630|title=Lithuania seeking funding for Eurovision 2010|last=Hondal|first=Victor|date=2009-12-15|publisher=ESCToday|accessdate=15 December 2009|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091217234754/http://www.esctoday.com/news/read/14630|archivedate=17 December 2009}}</ref> Ultimately, private company TEO LT provided the necessary funding and Lithuania participated in B\u00e6rum.\n\nIn 2011 Lithuania participated in the first semi-final on the 10 May 2011 and after coming fifth, qualified for the Final. In the final, Lithuania received 63 points, to finish 19th.\n\nIn 2012, Lithuania qualified for the final placing 3rd with 104 points [[Donny Montell]] finished 14th in the Grand Final with the song \"[[Love Is Blind (Donny Montell song)|Love Is Blind]]\".\n\nIn 2013,Lithuania quafiled to the final,he placed 9th in the first semi-final, with 53 points, qualifying Lithuania to the finals for the 3rd time in row.In the final,he ended on 22nd place with 17 points.\n\nIn 2014,Vilija didn't qualify to final finishing 11th of 15 entrants in the second semi-final, scoring 36 points.\n\nIn 2016 Donny Montell returned to the contest in 2016 and achieved Lithuania's best result of the decade so far, finishing ninth with the song \"[[I've Been Waiting for This Night]]\". In 2018, [[Ieva Zasimauskait\u0117]] achieved Lithuania's fifth top 15 result, finishing 12th with \"[[When We're Old (Ieva Zasimauskait\u0117 song)|When We're Old]]\".\n\nAs of 2019, Lithuania remains the only Baltic country not to win the contest after wins for Estonia in 2001 and Latvia in 2002. However, since the introduction of the semifinal round in 2004, Lithuania has more final appearances than the other Baltic nations, with nine, compared to seven for Estonia and six for Latvia.\n\n== Contestants ==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Table key\n|-\n|width=15px bgcolor=gold|{{center|1}}\n|Winner\n|-\n|bgcolor=silver|{{center|2}}\n|Second place\n|-\n|bgcolor=#c96|{{center|3}}\n|Third place\n|-\n|bgcolor=#FE8080|{{center|\u25c1}}\n|Last place\n|-\n|bgcolor=#87A96B|{{small|{{center|{{Abbr|W.|Withdrew}}}}}}\n|Withdrew/disqualified\n|}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\"\n|-\n!width=30px|Year\n!Artist\n!Language\n!Song\n!width=50px|Final\n!width=50px|Points\n!width=50px|Semi\n!width=50px|Points\n|- bgcolor=\"#FE8080\"\n!{{Escyr|1994}}\n|[[Ovidijus Vy\u0161niauskas]]\n|[[Lithuanian language|Lithuanian]]\n|\"[[Lop\u0161in\u0117 mylimai]]\"\n|align=center|25 \u25c1\n|align=center|0\n|colspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"99999\" {{N/A|No semi-finals}}\n|-bgcolor=\"#DCDCDC\"\n|colspan=\"8\" data-sort-value=\"zzzzz\" {{N/A|Did not participate between {{ESCYr|1995}} and {{ESCYr|1998}}}}\n|-\n!{{Escyr|1999}}\n|[[Aist\u0117 Smilgevi\u010di\u016bt\u0117|Aist\u0117]]\n|[[Samogitian dialect|Samogitian]]\n|\"[[Strazdas]]\"\n|align=center|20\n|align=center|13\n|colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"5\" data-sort-value=\"99999\" {{N/A|No semi-finals}}\n|-\n|{{N/A|{{Escyr|2000}}}}\n|colspan=\"5\" {{N/A|Did not participate}}\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2001}}\n|[[SKAMP]]\n|[[English language|English]], Lithuanian\n|\"[[You Got Style]]\"\n|align=center|13\n|align=center|35\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2002}}\n|[[Aivaras Stepukonis|Aivaras]]\n|English\n|\"[[Happy You]]\"\n|align=center|23\n|align=center|12\n|-\n|{{N/A|{{Escyr|2003}}}}\n|colspan=\"5\" {{N/A|Did not participate}}\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2004}}\n|[[Linas and Simona]]\n|English\n|\"[[What's Happened to Your Love?]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|16\n|align=center|26\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2005}}\n|[[Laura & The Lovers]]\n|English\n|\"[[Little by Little (Laura and The Lovers song)|Little by Little]]\"\n|bgcolor=\"#FE8080\" align=center|25 \u25c1\n|bgcolor=\"#FE8080\" align=center|17\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2006}}\n|[[LT United]]\n|English{{efn|Includes two phrases in [[French language|French]].}}\n|\"[[We Are the Winners]]\"\n|align=center|6\n|align=center|162\n|align=center|5\n|align=center|163\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2007}}\n|[[4Fun]]\n|English\n|\"[[Love or Leave]]\"\n|align=center|21\n|align=center|28\n|colspan=\"2\" data-sort-value=\"-9999\" {{N/A|Top 10 Previous Year}}{{efn|name=note2|According to the [[Rules of the Eurovision Song Contest|then-Eurovision rules]], the top ten non-[[Eurovision Song Contest#Big Four and Big Five|Big Four]] countries from the previous year along with the Big Four automatically qualified for the Grand Final without having to compete in semi-finals. For example, if Germany and France placed inside the top ten, the 11th and 12th spots were advanced to next year's Grand Final along with all countries ranked in the top ten.}}\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2008}}\n|[[Jeronimas Milius]]\n|English\n|\"[[Nomads in the Night]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|16\n|align=center|30\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2009}}\n|[[Sasha Son]]\n|English, [[Russian language|Russian]]\n|\"[[Love (Sasha Son song)|Love]]\"\n|align=center|23\n|align=center|23\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|66\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2010}}\n|[[InCulto]]\n|English\n|\"[[Eastern European Funk]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|12\n|align=center|44\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2011}}\n|[[Evelina Sa\u0161enko]]\n|English{{Efn|Also contains phrases in French, and [[American Sign Language]] was also used in the live performance.}}\n|\"[[C'est ma vie]]\"\n|align=center|19\n|align=center|63\n|align=center|5\n|align=center|81\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2012}}\n|[[Donny Montell]]\n|English\n|\"[[Love Is Blind (Donny Montell song)|Love Is Blind]]\"\n|align=center|14\n|align=center|70\n|bgcolor=\"#CC9966\" align=center|3\n|bgcolor=\"#CC9966\" align=center|104\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2013}}\n|[[Andrius Pojavis]]\n|English\n|\"[[Something (Andrius Pojavis song)|Something]]\"\n|align=center|22\n|align=center|17\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|53\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2014}}\n|[[Vilija Mata\u010di\u016bnait\u0117|Vilija]]\n|English\n|\"[[Attention (Vilija Mata\u010di\u016bnait\u0117 song)|Attention]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|11\n|align=center|36\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2015}}\n|[[Monika Linkyt\u0117]] & [[Vaidas Baumila]]\n|English\n|\"[[This Time (Monika Linkyt\u0117 & Vaidas Baumila song)|This Time]]\"\n|align=center|18\n|align=center|30\n|align=center|7\n|align=center|67\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2016}}\n|[[Donny Montell]]\n|English\n|\"[[I've Been Waiting for This Night]]\"\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|200\n|align=center|4\n|align=center|222\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2017}}\n|[[Fusedmarc]]\n|English\n|\"[[Rain of Revolution]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|17\n|align=center|42\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2018}}\n|[[Ieva Zasimauskait\u0117]]\n|English{{efn|Contains two lines in Lithuanian.}}\n|\"[[When We're Old (Ieva Zasimauskait\u0117 song)|When We're Old]]\"\n|align=center|12\n|align=center|181\n|align=center|9\n|align=center|119\n|-\n!{{Escyr|2019}}\n|[[Jurijus Veklenko|Jurij Veklenko]]\n|English\n|\"[[Run with the Lions]]\"\n|colspan=\"2\" {{N/A|Failed to qualify}}\n|align=center|11\n|align=center|93\n|-bgcolor=\"#87A96B\"\n|{{N/A|{{Escyr|2020}}}}{{Efn|2020 contest was cancelled due to 2019-20 pandemic of Coronavirus.}}\n|[[The Roop]]\n|English\n|\"[[On Fire (The Roop song)|On Fire]]\"\n|colspan=\"4\" {{N/A|Cancelled}}\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n===Barbara Dex Award===\n{{further|Barbara Dex Award}}\n{|class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!Year\n!Performer\n!Host city\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|2014}}\n|[[Vilija Mata\u010di\u016bnait\u0117]]\n|{{flagicon|Denmark}} [[Copenhagen]]\n|{{center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wiwibloggs.com/2015/07/09/poll-worst-dressed-barbara-dex-award-winner/|title=Poll: Who was the worst dressed Barbara Dex Award winner?|publisher=[[Wiwibloggs]]|date=9 July 2015|accessdate=8 December 2019|first=William Lee|last=Adams}}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n==Related involvement==\n===Commentators and spokespersons===\n{{more citations needed section|date=December 2019}}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Commentator\n!Spokesperson\n!class=\"unsortable\"|{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1994}}\n|[[Darius U\u017ekuraitis]] ||Gitana Lapinskait\u0117 ||\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|{{Escyr|1995}}-{{Escyr|1998}}\n|{{n/a|No broadcast}} ||{{n/a|Did not participate}} ||\n|